WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en-GB

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:02.000
And anything fleeing from the kraits

00:00:02.000 --> 00:00:05.520
will swim straight into the mouths of the waiting trevally.

00:00:06.600 --> 00:00:08.320
There's nowhere to hide.

00:00:14.640 --> 00:00:17.160
And there are snakes here, too.

00:00:17.720 --> 00:00:18.840
Lots of them.

00:00:24.440 --> 00:00:27.520
These are banded sea kraits.

00:00:28.080 --> 00:00:32.760
They lay their eggs on land,
but they hunt here in the water.

00:00:37.480 --> 00:00:40.920
They're too slow to catch fish in the straight chase,

00:00:41.000 --> 00:00:45.760
so they seek prey that is hiding in the nooks
and crannies of the coral.

00:00:48.280 --> 00:00:52.240
Their bite is highly venomous
and paralyses their victims.

00:00:57.360 --> 00:00:58.840
And on this reef,

00:00:58.840 --> 00:01:01.960
the snakes do not hunt alone.

00:01:07.520 --> 00:01:12.600
Shoals of yellow goatfish and trevally 
are seeking similar prey 

00:01:12.600 --> 00:01:15.680
and they attract the snake's attention.

00:01:15.680 --> 00:01:18.560
As one group of hunters searches the reef,

00:01:18.560 --> 00:01:20.320
they're joined by the other.

00:01:28.720 --> 00:01:33.040
At least 30 snakes have now joined the caravan.

00:01:38.840 --> 00:01:42.200
The big fish scare the prey into cracks.

00:01:42.280 --> 00:01:45.160
And there the snakes can catch them.

00:01:45.520 --> 00:01:47.520
And anything fleeing from the kraits,

00:01:47.520 --> 00:01:50.880
will swim straight into the mouths of the waiting trevally.

00:01:52.360 --> 00:01:54.040
There's nowhere to hide.

00:01:59.680 --> 00:02:02.440
As the raiders scour the reef,

00:02:02.440 --> 00:02:05.360
more and more snakes join the hunt.

00:02:26.560 --> 00:02:29.800
This cooperation between snakes and fish,

00:02:29.800 --> 00:02:31.520
spectacular though it is,

00:02:31.520 --> 00:02:33.720
has only recently been observed.

00:02:33.760 --> 00:02:37.960
For it only happens on the most 
remote reefs in Indonesia.

00:02:47.240 --> 00:02:51.000
Perhaps such hunting alliances 
were once a common sight.

00:02:51.080 --> 00:02:57.000
But today, no more than 6% of Indonesia's reefs 
are in their pristine state.

